      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Combining melatonin with Zolpidem isn't something you should do without consulting your doctor first. Both substances aim to induce sleep, and taking them together could potentially amplify sedative effects too much, leading to morning grogginess. Your doctor prescribed Zolpidem for a reason, so it's best to stick to their instructions for that medication. Tell them about your melatonin use so they can create a safe plan for improving your sleep quality!",
