      "content": "Even if you feel fine now, adding more sleep aids is counterintuitive and potentially risky, even in small doses. A little melatonin won't magically prevent waking up; that's a deeper issue needing a different approach. Instead of doubling down on pills, try optimizing your sleep hygiene—think cooling your room and ditching screens an hour before bed. A quick chat with your physician about your specific middle-of-the-night wake-ups is the smartest next step!",
      "source": "target",
